<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">VST mourns the passing of Bishop James Cruickshank</h1>
<img class="size-full" src="http://vst.edu/wp-content/themes/vst/img/lazy.jpg" data-src="http://vst.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Jim-Cruickshank.jpg"/>

<p><span style="color: #141823;">VST is saddened to hear of the passing of <strong>Bishop James Cruickshank</strong>, former <strong>Director of Continuing Education</strong> and subsequently <strong>Vice Principal and Professor of Pastoral Theology</strong>, on December 30, 2015. Jim Cruickshank was well known to many and remained a faithful friend to VST in his retirement, during which time he continued to teach. We offer our condolences to his family and friends.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #141823;">A&nbsp;Requiem Eucharist will be held at Christ Church Cathedral, 690 Burrard Street, at 3 pm on Saturday, January 16th. There is also a possibility that the service will be live streamed on the website of the cathedral. Please check their website for updates at&nbsp;</span><a style="color: #3b5998;" href="http://thecathedral.ca/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://thecathedral.ca/</a></p>
<p><span style="color: #141823;">More details can be found at <a href="http://www.vancouver.anglican.ca/news/james-david-cruickshank-1936-2015." target="_blank">http://www.vancouver.anglican.ca/news/james-david-cruickshank-1936-2015.</a></span></p>
